content:
State Police, Orange County district attorney confirm the suspect who shot a local police chief this morning is dead. 

Arnold "Butch" Amthor of the Town of Montgomery police department was shot in the shoulder responding to a domestic disturbance. He's expected to make a full recovery. 

It is unclear whether the suspect was killed by officers who returned fire, or by a self-inflicted gunshot

content:
Sentencing day for a Rockland County podiatrist and his girlfriend. Ira Bernstein and Kelli Gribluk plotted to pay a hit man $100,000 to kill his wife.  Instead that hit man went to police. 

This morning the target of the plot, Susan Bernstein, told the judge her husband is a "murderer who got caught."  Bernstein will serve 5-15 years in prison, Gribluk 4-12 years.
name: Marcus Solis
title: Timeline Photos

content: And so it ends for a once prominent podiatrist in Rockland County.  Ira Bernstein was sentenced to 5 to 15 years in prison for plotting to kill his wife.  Bernstein's girlfriend Kelli Gribluk will serve 4 to 12 years.
name: Marcus Solis
